      "date": "2017-11-14 15:29:59.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\nnot sure what reference you meant, but OSD doesn't block inode/dnode removal. instead a flag is set and any subsequent access returns an error.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "9d3846068566f83ba725c8840f24933ccebdf751",
      "author": {
        "_account_id": 3,
        "name": "Fan Yong",
        "email": "fan.yong@intel.com",
        "username": "nasf",
        "inactive": true
      },
      "date": "2017-11-14 15:56:34.000000000",
      "message": "Patch Set 2:\n\n> not sure what reference you meant, but OSD doesn't block inode/dnode removal. instead a flag is set and any subsequent access returns an error.\n\nI mean that as long as the object is not freed, its referenced inode/dnode will not be destroyed.\nOn the other hand, the mdt_dom_write_lock is taken on the mdt_object that will not affect OSD level behavior, means it will not block the mdt_reint_unlink() operation.",
      "accounts_in_message": [],
      "_revision_number": 2
    },
    {
      "id": "b4663d873c7011983677f6f51c09d4e8ac75bdda",
      "author": {
